FBIS4-1234 "drafr079_c_94068" FBIS-AFR-94-079 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Britain's Prince Philip To Attend Inauguration Britain's Prince Philip To Attend Inauguration MB2104193494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 21 Apr 94 MB2104193494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] Queen Elizabeth will be represented by her consort, Prince Philip, at the swearing in of South Africa's new president on the 10th of next month, ending a 47-year-old break in official visits by Britain's royal family. This was announce by Buckingham palace in London today. In 1947 King George VI visited South Africa with his consort and daughters, Elizabeth, now queen, and Margaret.
